# VedicRGI Cursor Rules — chitta (Reflex / Fast Path)
This repo is **Chitta (Memory)** + the **FAST-path router**. It must enforce the VedicRGI reliability posture.

## Neti, Neti (anti-hallucination)
- Prefer **"Data Missing"** over guessing.
- Never fabricate memories; if retrieval is weak, return empty results + low confidence.

## Privacy + encryption
- Treat all memory content as sensitive.
- Do not log raw memory payloads unnecessarily.
- Preserve encryption-at-rest invariants (vault outputs must remain encrypted).

## Tripartite graph invariants (strict)
- Schema is typed: Context / Moment / Sensor.
- Do not introduce “generic KG” drift; add types deliberately.
- Any schema change must come with a migration or be strictly additive.

## FAST vs DEEP contract
- FAST is only for familiar, high-confidence queries (identity, preferences, summaries).
- URL/tool-intent prompts should route **DEEP** (deterministic), not FAST.

## Ops + environment
- Primary working copy: `/Users/VedicRGI_Worker/chitta`.
- Router listens locally (e.g., `127.0.0.1:18800`).
- Keep router responses structured and stable (decision/route/confidence + counts).

## Repo hygiene
- Keep dependencies minimal.
- Avoid committing generated artifacts (`__pycache__`, logs, local envs).
- Remote: `git@github.com:vedicrgi/chitta.git`.
